page.title: 10Clements Tump
page.content: MRS.NASH WAS 4 WEEKS OLD WHEN SHE CAME TO CLEMENTS TUMP TO LIVE WITH THE FAMILY.SHE LIVED THERE 27 YEARS.MRS.NASH HAD NINE SISTERS AND THREE BROTHERS.HER FATHER WILLIAM BAKER WHO WAS DEPUTY AT THE PRINCESS ROYAL COLLIERY.HER MOTHER EMILY BAKER LOOKED AFTER THE FAMILY AND DID THE HOUSE WORK.MRS.NASH'S FATHER HAD A SPARE TIME JOB AS A LOCAL BUTCHER,THEREFORE HE WAS KNOWN HAS "BUTCHER BAKER." AT 5 YEARS OLD MRS.NASH WENT TO BREAM INFANTS SCHOOL.SHE WALKED TO SCHOOL WITH OTHER C ILDREN BECAUSE THERE WAS NO TRANSPORT.THE HOUSE MRS.NASH LIVED IN WAS SURROUNDED BY WOODLANDS,THERE WAS ALOT OF TRACKS IN THE WOODS TO WALK ON.WHEN MRS.NASH WAS 10 YEARS OLD,SHE WENT TO GATHER PIECES OF WOOD FOR THE FIRE.AT 11 YEARS OLD SHE WENT
